      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear u about the retraining stuff but it feels like u're saying the bill is basically a good thing and just the \"interests\" are the problem. if u were just looking at it from an economic standpoint without the climate part, wouldn't cutting subsidies for a whole industry that's still active be a massive risk for the local economy? like, is there any world where the \"outdated\" side has a valid economic argument or is it just political?",
